### Refund Policy API Scenario Verification REST Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/v1
@authToken = YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE

###
# 1. Fetch Refund Policies List (All available: Global + Custom)
GET {{baseUrl}}/refund-policy/list
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###
# 2. Fetch Refund Policies List Filtered for EVENTS
# Should return global policies (type: both) plus any event-specific policies.
GET {{baseUrl}}/refund-policy/list?type=event
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###
# 3. Fetch Refund Policies List Filtered for COURSES
# Should return global policies (type: both) plus any course-specific policies.
GET {{baseUrl}}/refund-policy/list?type=course
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###
# 4. Create a Custom Refund Policy (as Organizer)
# @name createPolicy
POST {{baseUrl}}/refund-policy/create
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Custom Organizer Refund Policy",
  "description": "Custom organizer 3-day partial 75% refund policy.",
  "refundPercentage": 75,
  "daysBefore": 3,
  "type": "event",
  "isGlobal": false
}

### Store the created policy ID for subsequent requests
@policyId = {{createPolicy.response.body.policy._id}}

###
# 5. Fetch Refund Policy Details
GET {{baseUrl}}/refund-policy/detail/{{policyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###
# 6. Edit Custom Refund Policy
POST {{baseUrl}}/refund-policy/edit/{{policyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Custom Organizer Refund Policy",
  "refundPercentage": 80
}

###
# 7. Create Event with Valid Refund Policy (Success Scenario)
POST {{baseUrl}}/event/create
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventTitle": "Success Case Event",
  "shortDescription": "Short description.",
  "description": "Detailed description.",
  "startDate": "2027-01-01T12:00:00.000Z",
  "startTime": "12:00",
  "endDate": "2027-01-01T14:00:00.000Z",
  "endTime": "14:00",
  "venueName": "Virtual Verification Venue",
  "refundPolicy": "{{policyId}}",
  "isDraft": true
}

###
# 8. Create Event with Course-Only Refund Policy (Should Fail Check)
# First we create a course-only policy
# @name createCoursePolicy
POST {{baseUrl}}/refund-policy/create
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Course Only Refund",
  "description": "Refund only for courses.",
  "refundPercentage": 100,
  "daysBefore": 5,
  "type": "course",
  "isGlobal": false
}

### Store the course-only policy ID
@coursePolicyId = {{createCoursePolicy.response.body.policy._id}}

### Now try to attach it to an Event (Should fail with 400 Bad Request)
POST {{baseUrl}}/event/create
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventTitle": "Fail Case Event",
  "shortDescription": "Short description.",
  "description": "Detailed description.",
  "startDate": "2027-01-01T12:00:00.000Z",
  "startTime": "12:00",
  "endDate": "2027-01-01T14:00:00.000Z",
  "endTime": "14:00",
  "venueName": "Virtual Verification Venue",
  "refundPolicy": "{{coursePolicyId}}",
  "isDraft": true
}

###
# 9. Create Event with Non-Existent Refund Policy (Should Fail Check with 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/event/create
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventTitle": "Non-Existent Fail Event",
  "shortDescription": "Short description.",
  "description": "Detailed description.",
  "startDate": "2027-01-01T12:00:00.000Z",
  "startTime": "12:00",
  "endDate": "2027-01-01T14:00:00.000Z",
  "endTime": "14:00",
  "venueName": "Virtual Verification Venue",
  "refundPolicy": "60a1b2c3d4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1",
  "isDraft": true
}

###
# 10. Delete Custom Refund Policy
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/refund-policy/delete/{{policyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
